#Text=Plymouth ( Minnesota )
#Text=Plymouth is a city located in the heart of Minnesota .
#Text=This city is place that has a good solid community and friendly people .
#Text=Plymouth has a lot to offer both its residents and its travelers .
#Text=They are known for having affordable housing , low crime rates and most importantly an active outdoor culture .
#Text=Plymouth was also Money Magazine 's best place to live in 2008 .
#Text=If Plymouth was ranked as the number one place to live , it must be a really great place to travel to as well .
#Text=By plane
#Text=The Minneapolis/St .
#Text=Paul International Airport is only fifteen miles from Plymouth .
#Text=There are numerous taxis in Plymouth taking travelers to and from their destinations .
#Text=Automobiles are the most common type of transportation for travelers who are staying in the city and need to get around .
#Text=By car
#Text=Interstate 494 runs through the city and connects to Interstate 94 just north of Plymouth in the city of Maple Grove .
#Text=U.S. Highway 169 runs along the eastern edge of town .
#Text=See
#Text=Something special in Plymouth that all travelers to the city should see is its open-air amphitheater .
#Text=The Hilde Performance Center is located right in Plymouth and holds numerous summer concerts .
#Text=This is definitely a fun and exciting place that all tourists should visit during the course of their trip .
#Text=In February , Plymouth hosts its annual Fire and Ice Festival .
#Text=Attendees can play mini-golf , basketball and go bowling , all right on the ice .
#Text=Do
#Text=Plymouth has a lot to offer tourists when it comes to its parks and recreation .
#Text=The city of Plymouth has the Recreation Division , the Park Maintenance Division , the Plymouth Creek Center and Field house , and the Plymouth Ice Center .
#Text=The city has done a lot over the years to spruce up its recreation division .
#Text=The Recreation Division offers many programs , classes and events for people of all ages .
#Text=Sky Zone Minneapolis .
#Text=- located in Plymouth
#Text=Buy
#Text=Shopping is a fun thing to do in Plymouth .
#Text=With the Mall of America nearby , going shopping is always an option if you want something fun to do on your trip here .
#Text=Eat
#Text=There are a ton of restaurants and places to eat in Plymouth .
#Text=There are full-service restaurants like Chili 's and T.G.I Fridays .
#Text=There are Chinese and Thai restaurants .
#Text=Like most places , Plymouth has a plenty of fast-food restaurants to choose from as well .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=There are a lot of hotels in Plymouth and all are reasonably priced .
#Text=Some hotels are : Radisson Hotel and Conference Center , the Country Inn and Suites , the Comfort Inn , and the Red Roof Inn and Suites .
